<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p><rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> with moulding above and below on front and right side, still partly buried, broken away to left (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.07</measure> visible × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.75</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.60</measure>).</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p><measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.04</measure></p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="-0027" notAfter="0050" exact="both">27 B.C-A.D. 50</date>
(<rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>)</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="emperor" full="yes"><persName type="divine" reg="Ζεύς" full="yes"><name reg="Ζεύς">Δία</name>  <w lemma="πατρῷος">Πατρῷον</w></persName>  <lb n="2"/><w lemma="σεβαστός">Σεβαστὸν</w>  <name reg="Καῖσαρ">Καίσαρα</name></persName>  <lb n="2a"/><space unit="line" extent="1" dim="horizontal"/></ab>
</div>
<div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Transcription (Reynolds); Gaudin's squeeze (checked); publications.</p>
</div>
<div type="apparatus">
<head>Apparatus</head>
<p>l. 1, Reinach, with an incomplete squeeze, and not knowing that the stone was complete proposed <foreign lang="grc"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλλω</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ν</unclear>α Πατρῷον</foreign>; Robert corrected this (in his first article) and then saw that Kubitschek and Reichel already gave the corect reading.</p>
</div>
<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>(Statue of) Zeus of our Ancestors, Augustus Caesar.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>For the expression cf:
Nero at Smyrna, Smyrna 1, l. 5, 
<foreign lang="grc">Τιβερίου Κλαυδίου Ἡρω<supplied reason="lost">^  ἀρχιερέως</supplied> καὶ σεβαστοφάντου καὶ [διὰ βίου ἀγωνοθέτου] θεᾶς Ῥώμης καὶ θεοῦ [Σεβαστοῦ Καίσαρος] 
Διὸς Πατρ'ου αὐτοκ[ράτορος καὶ ἀρχιερέως] μεγίστου, πατρὸς τῆ[ς πατρίδος καὶ σωτῆρος?] τοῦ σύμπαντος ἀν<unclear reason="damage">θ</unclear>[ρώπων γένους
</foreign></p><p>Halicarnassus: GIBM894, 4-7
<foreign lang="grc">Καίσαρα τὸν Σεβαστὸν ἐνεν[κ]αμένη [τ]ὸ[ν] τῷ καθ′ ἡμᾶς εὐδαίμονι βίωι πατέρα μὲν τῆς [ἑαυ]τοῦ πατ[ρ]ίδος θεᾶς Ῥώμης, Δία δὲ πατρῶον καὶ σωτῆρα τοῦ κο[ι] [ν]οῦ τῶν ἀνθρώπων γένους</foreign></p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p>
<rs type="origLocation">Unknown</rs>
<rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Walls, West</rs>: reused south of the West gate.</rs>
<rs type="lastLocation">Findspot</rs>
</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>Recorded by Kubitschek (KV.13, Abklatsch 44) and by Reichel (RI.5v ); by Gaudin (37); recorded by the MAMA expedition in 1934; recorded by the NYU expedition in 1973 (SBI <rs type="sbi">97</rs>).</p>
</div>
